It happened that continual rain fell during the first few days of Cicero's stay at Arpinum, so he employed his whole time in editing afresh the Academica, which he now divided into four books instead of two, making the interlocutors himself, Varro and Atticus'. The position occupied by Atticus in the dialogue was quite second· ary, but he was so well pleased with it that Cicero determined to confer on him often in the future such minor parts⁸.
